-- Fabio Capello Signs Two-Year Contract as Russia Soccer Manager
-- B y   S t e p a n   K r a v c h e n k o
-- 2012-07-26T13:09:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-26/fabio-capello-signs-two-year-contract-as-russia-soccer-manager.html
Former England soccer coach  Fabio Capello  signed a two-year contract to manage the Russian
national team today, according to a statement on the Russian
Football Union website.  Dick Advocaat left the post after the Euro 2012 tournament,
in which his team failed to reach the quarterfinals.  Capello, 66, quit as England manager in February. The
Italian was a club coach at AC Milan, Real Madrid, Roma and
Juventus.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stepan Kravchenko in Moscow at 
